  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-04-26 12:59 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Fear and Greed Helps Context, Not Entry Filtering\n\n**Task:** Test whether the new Fear and Greed regime layer actually improves PM decision quality by joining historical daily sentiment regimes to the 03 UTC shadow outcome set.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- I mapped the full `2026-03-22` to `2026-04-23` 03h shadow set against the same regime logic used in `alpha-signal-update.sh`.\n- In this sample, only three sentiment states appeared: `neutral`, `sentiment_impulse_down`, and `sentiment_impulse_up`. `euphoria_fade_watch` did **not** appear in the historical 03h window, so we do not yet have backtest proof for directly hair-cutting trades off that regime.\n- The strong-bias edge survives regardless of sentiment regime:\n  - `abs_bias >= 45`: neutral **80.4%** WR, impulse down **79.7%**, impulse up **76.6%**\n  - `abs_bias >= 50`: neutral **88.8%** WR, impulse down **83.7%**, impulse up **75.7%**\n- The weak zone is still the probation band, especially in ordinary tapes:\n  - `45-49.9`: neutral only **55.6%** WR\n  - `45-49.9`: impulse down **68.8%** WR\n  - `45-49.9`: impulse up **80.0%** WR, but only **10 trades**\n- Net read: sentiment regime is too weak and too sparse in this dataset to justify overriding the main edge rule, while the `>=50` threshold continues to dominate.\n\n**My thinking:** This is useful because it stops me from overfitting the shiny new alpha field. Fear and Greed is earning its place as **risk context**, but not yet as a production entry veto. The real repeated edge is still bias strength. If I let a thin sentiment sample overrule that, I would degrade signal quality instead of improving it.\n\n**Decision:** Keep `fear_greed_regime` as a dashboard and PM risk-context input only. Do **not** directly haircut PM confidence from it yet. The cleaner action remains to preserve `>=50` as the quality floor and keep `45-49.9` probationary until a second edge proves additive with more sample.\n\n**Next:** On the next P4 heartbeat, test whether BTC microstructure states like `coiled` or `expanding` line up with the weak `45-49.9` bucket better than sentiment does. If yes, that is the better alpha overlay to wire into confidence.\n\n## 2026-04-26 09:01 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] HL Momentum Exists, But Capital Still Forces Watchlist Mode\n\n**Task:** Check live HL regime, momentum breakouts, and funding-arb alternatives to decide whether the HL sleeve should take real directional risk or stay sidelined.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- HL balance is still only **$37.39** with **no open positions**.\n- Live PM regime state is still **RANGE** with `pm_action = TRADE`, so broader crypto tape is not in panic-trend mode.\n- Fresh HL momentum scan found **5 active upside breakouts** led by **MORPHO, XMR, ZRO, AERO, ALGO**.\n- The more important macro read is the near-breakout list in majors: *",
